Chhattisgarh: Six naxals killed, AK rifle recovered in Dantewada encounter 
18-3-2017 
An encounter broke out between security forces and naxals on Saturday in Chhattisgarh’s Dantewada district. According to news agency ANI, the encounter is presently underway and six naxals has been killed while body of one naxalite and one AK-47 rifle along with other arms and ammunition has been recovered from Burdum area. This comes just a day after two naxals were gunned down by police on Thursday in an encounter with the security forces in Narayanpur district.

According to officials, the encounter took place early today in the Burgam village when a joint squad of CRPF and District Reserve Group (DRG) of state police was out for operations. “The encounter is still on. A Naxal has been killed and an AK series assault rifle has been recovered,” a senior officer told PTI.

Reinforcement teams have been rushed in, officials said, adding reports from the spot are coming in delayed as the

encounter area is in interior forests of the Dantewada district in south Bastar. The 111 battalion of Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) is leading the operation, they said.

WITH PTI INPUTS

